From Ron Phillips Subject Armed Citizen April ' THE ARMED CITIZEN Mere presence of a firearm without a shot being fired prevents crime in many instances as shown by news reports sent to The Armed Shooting usually can be justified only where crime constitutes an immediate imminent threat to life or limb or in some circumstances The accounts below are from clippings sent in by NRA Anyone is free to quote or reproduce Retired Las Vegas deputy police chief Larry Bolden initially tried to defend himself with a steering wheel bar lock when a criminal attacked him in his But then the intruder wrestled it from him Bolden pulled his pistol and fired several times wounding his attacker and stopping the He was just a citizen defending himself a police official The Review Journal Las Vegas A pair of teenaged robbers armed with a sawed off shotgun and handguns took the day's receipts from Brooklyn bodega owner Hector As they made their getaway Martinez grabbed his registered gauge shotgun and gave When one fired Martinez returned three blasts slightly wounding his They fled but were apprehended when they sought medical Newsday Long Island A sign posted on the door of Roman Paras' shop reads The owners of this property are armed and highly skilled to protect life liberty and property from criminal Apparently a pair of robbers didn't pause to read it as they threatened Paras' wife in their Oxnard convenience Hearing her scream Paras grabbed his ran to the front of the store and shot it out with the masked and armed men killing one The Times Los Angeles Anne Marie Sullivan was showering in her Portland home one morning when she heard the front door crash She jumped out of the shower in time to see a man entering the Running to the bedroom Sullivan retrieved her boyfriend's pistol and fired two shots mortally wounding the The dead man had a lengthy police and prison The Oregonian Portland Mike Baranelli would have let two robbers who burst into a Birmingham barber shop keep his But the year old retired teacher was unwilling to surrender his When the intruders ordered Baranelli the shop owner and another man to lie on the floor Baranelli pulled his pistol and shot both men in the head killing I felt sure there was going to be three dead people in I think I had some divine help Baranelli The Sunday Advertiser Montgomery Believing an elderly Harvey couple would again be easy prey a knife wielding home invader instead met death when the year old homeowner loosed three rounds from a semi automatic Police said the dead man had been charged several times for thefts from the couple's The Star Chicago Heights The criminal's profile was scheduled to appear on America's Most Wanted but his shot at fame was abruptly canceled by a Hallandale service station The Michigan prison escapee walked into the station and announced a Instead of cash he got bullets in the head and chest from station clerk Gary Police said McVey acted in self defense and would not face The Sun Sentinel Lauderdale A Bridgeport oil delivery man handed over the few dollars he But the thug apparently unsatisfied with his take turned his gun on his victim and demanded more Instead of more cash the deliveryman instead pulled his own pistol and fired mortally wounding the Police said the dead man had held up a nearby market just before the fatal The Courant Hartford After repeated burglaries at her San Marcos home Joan Vessel was ready with a and a cordless phone when she heard glass breaking one When she found two teenagers attempting to get into her woodshed Vessel fired a warning shot over their heads marched them into the front yard and called The Times Advocate Escondido Angry that his auto insurance had been canceled a client used brass knuckles to take it out on Brandon agent Steven When his assailant walked out of the office Taylor grabbed a pistol kept there and held the former client at gun point until police The Tribune Tampa Dozing one evening at his Exeter office Jim Pisano was 